The paper deals with the identification of parameters for torque-based control in humanoid robots, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of partial least-square (PLS) regression for the identification process suggests a focus on system identification and control (cs.SY). The paper also mentions the use of machine learning techniques, which could fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the use of a 6-axis force/torque sensor suggests a possible application in computer vision (cs.CV) for object manipulation and interaction.
